<subSubSection pageId="36" pageNumber="37" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="36.[151,1437,979,1113]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<bibRefCitation author="Sundukov, Yu. N." box="[151,349,1015,1041]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" pagination="20 - 117" refId="ref79858" refString="Sundukov, Yu. N. (2017) Suborder Symphyta - Sawflies and wood wasps. In: Lelej, A. S., Proshchalykin, M. Yu. &amp; Loktionov, V. M. (Eds.), Annotated catalogue of the Hymenoptera of Russia. Vol. I. Symphyta and Apocrita: Aculeata. Proceedings of the Zoological Institute of the Russian Academy of Sciences, Supplement 6, pp. 20 - 117." type="journal article" year="2017">Sundukov (2017)</bibRefCitation>
noted “ 
<collectingCountry box="[441,522,1015,1041]" name="Russia" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Russia</collectingCountry>
: without regions (Taeger, Blank, 2011)” in the distribution of this species. This record is wrong, as explained under 
<taxonomicName box="[564,706,1052,1078]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Onycholyda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yezoensis">
<emphasis box="[564,706,1052,1078]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">O. yezoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
below. There is no evidence for the occurrence of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Takeuchi" baseAuthorityYear="1930" box="[1284,1437,1051,1078]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Onycholyda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minomalis">
<emphasis box="[1284,1437,1051,1078]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">O. minomalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[180,258,1087,1113]" name="Russia" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Russia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
